There is something a bit &quot;odd&quot; with your models. The `ForeignKey` from `Tb2` to `Tb1` is a `primary_key=True` as well. This thus means that this `ForeignKey` is unique, and therefore there can only be (at most) one `Tb2` that links to a `Tb1`. This thus means that the `COUNT(DISTINCT p.version)` will always be at most one.

You can however retrieve the maximum of the given version with:

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;Tb1.objects.filter(
    pk__in=[10, 9]
).annotate(
    &lt;b&gt;ver=Max(&#39;tb2__version&#39;)&lt;/b&gt;
)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

If there is *no* related `Tb2` instance, it will pass `None` to the `ver` attribute.

